1. System Requirements Check

Before starting, verify:

nproc        # Should be >= 4
free -h      # RAM >= 8GB
df -h        # Disk >= 40GB
 2. Create Stack User (MANDATORY)

DevStack must not run as root.

sudo adduser stack
sudo usermod -aG sudo stack

Switch user:

su - stack
 3. Install Dependencies
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y git vim net-tools
 4. Clone DevStack
git clone https://opendev.org/openstack/devstack.git
cd devstack
 5. Configure local.conf (VERY IMPORTANT)

Create the config file:

vim local.conf

Paste:

[[local|localrc]]

ADMIN_PASSWORD=Secr3tPass
DATABASE_PASSWORD=$ADMIN_PASSWORD
RABBIT_PASSWORD=$ADMIN_PASSWORD
SERVICE_PASSWORD=$ADMIN_PASSWORD

HOST_IP=192.168.56.101   # Replace with your VM IP

# Networking
FLOATING_RANGE=192.168.56.0/24
FIXED_RANGE=10.0.0.0/24
FIXED_NETWORK_SIZE=256

# Logging
LOGFILE=/opt/stack/logs/stack.sh.log

# Enable services
ENABLED_SERVICES=g-api,g-reg,key,n-api,n-crt,n-cpu,n-cond,n-sch,n-novnc,n-cauth,horizon,mysql,rabbit,q-svc,q-agt,q-dhcp,q-l3,q-meta,cinder,c-api,c-vol,c-sch

Get your VM IP:

ip a
 6. Run DevStack
./stack.sh

 Takes 20–40 minutes

If successful, you’ll see:

Horizon is now available at http://<HOST_IP>/dashboard
 7. Access OpenStack Dashboard (Horizon)

Open browser:

http://<HOST_IP>/dashboard

Login:

Username: admin
Password: Secr3tPass
 Core OpenStack Components (Important for Exams)
Component	Purpose
Keystone	Identity & authentication
Nova	Compute (VM instances)
Neutron	Networking
Glance	Image service
Cinder	Block storage
Horizon	Web dashboard
 8. Basic Operations
 A. Create Network

Dashboard:

Project → Network → Create Network

CLI:

source openrc admin admin

openstack network create private-net
openstack subnet create private-subnet \
  --network private-net \
  --subnet-range 10.0.0.0/24
 B. Launch Instance (VM)
Go to Compute → Instances → Launch Instance
Choose:
Image: Cirros / Ubuntu
Flavor: m1.small
Network: private-net

CLI:

openstack server create \
  --image cirros \
  --flavor m1.small \
  --network private-net \
  test-instance
 C. Create Volume (Cinder)
openstack volume create --size 1 test-volume

Attach:

openstack server add volume test-instance test-volume
 D. Assign Floating IP
openstack floating ip create public
openstack server add floating ip test-instance <IP>

sudo systemctl restart apache2


